  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>",
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;The following shall match those of the existing building in respect of materials used, detailed execution and finished appearance including type, size, colour, bond, pointing, coursing, jointing, profile and texture.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;a) Replacement windows&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON:&amp;nbsp; In order to retain the appearance and visual amenities of the conservation property.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Notwithstanding the approved plans, the replacement windows shall have glazing units with a profile (distance from outside edge of glazing to inside edge of glazing) of no more than 14mm, include integrated glazing bars and a putty finish and correct horn details and must not contain visible trickle vents or metallic/perforated spacer bars.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: To ensure that the proposal does not detract from the character and appearance of the conservation area.&lt;/p&gt;"
